description:
**We are looking for you!**
 We’re looking for a Senior UX Designer with a broader automotive and mobility domain background experience, who demonstrably can design simple yet highly engaging connected product experiences that push the limits of innovation and put the user in focus. Your global team of colleagues includes software and hardware technologists — together you will be tasked with creating industry-defining products.




**Skills and experience you can bring to this role!**
*Qualifications & experience:*
* A bachelor’s or master’s degree in the field of Service Design, Interaction Design, Design Thinking, UX Design, or another relevant program;
* 2-5 years of professional experience working in cross-disciplinary teams and guiding small teams of junior team members;
* Automotive & Mobility design experience (either with OEM/Tier1 or agency/consultancy) working in areas such as infotainment, navigation, ADAS, HMI, connected services, mobility, or other future mobility services;
* An intrinsic motivation to challenge the status-quo;
* The ability to think analytically and cross-pollinate ideas to novel solutions;
* A passion for human-centered design as a means to problem-solving;
* A profound understanding of the possibilities provided by digital technology;
* Empathy for the people you work with and the people you design for;
* The ability to express an optimistic spirit; because, above all, we need your smile and personality;
* Advanced knowledge of Swedish language;
* Upper-Intermediate level of English, both written and spoken.


*Nice to have:*
* Experience working with specific UX/UI design and prototyping tools for Automotive (e.g. Kanzi, Altia, Unreal Engine, CGI Studio, Unity, Android Auto, Apple CarPlay);
* Experience coding functional prototypes using JavaScript in combination with tools such as Framer and Axure;
* The ability to mock-up or prototype experiences in VR/AR; and
* Experience working within Agile software development teams.
* Experience working in some of our key business and technology domains: Financial services, Healthcare & life sciences, Media & Advertisement.


**What Impact You’ll Make**
* Collaborate proactively to achieve a joint effort;
* Act as an integral part of a cross-functional team;
* Communicate professionally and effectively in English (ideally, with proficiency in another language as well);
* Contribute to sales processes and client networking;
* Scope and manage projects and maintain and expand the client relationship;
* Manage project budgets and deadlines to remain on time and on target;
* Facilitate engaging co-creative workshops (virtually or in-person) with clients and team members to build a consensus and enable next steps;
* Lead 1-2 design projects simultaneously, overseeing team efforts to ensure projects are delivered to clients’ expectations;
* Master the full design process including user research, experience strategy and ideation, prototyping, validation and implementation;
* Master state-of-the-art UX design tools such as Figma and Adobe CC (Framer);
* Share your knowledge of design methods, tools and trends with the rest of the team.


**What You’ll Get**
 Regardless of your position or role, we have in place a wide array of benefits including flexible working (hybrid/remote models) and generous time off policies to make it easier for all people to thrive and succeed at Star. On top of that, we offer an extensive rewarding and compensation package, intellectually and creatively stimulating space and some more.




 Your holistic wellbeing is central at Star. You'll join a warm and vibrant multinational environment filled with impactful projects, career development opportunities, mentorship and training programs, fun sports activities, workshops, networking and outdoor meet-ups.

**We are looking for you!**
 We’re looking for a Senior Visual Designer. Based in Stockholm, you will join the organically growing team of designers who work across physical and digital product domains. Your global team of colleagues includes designers, strategists, software and hardware technologists — together you will be tasked with creating industry-defining products.




**Skills and experience you can bring to this role!**
*Qualifications & experience:*
* 4+ years of work experience;
* Automotive & Mobility design experience (either with OEM/Tier1 or agency/consultancy) working in areas such as infotainment, navigation, ADAS, HMI, connected services, mobility, or other future mobility services;
* An excellent portfolio showcasing experience design, interface design and visual design work for mobile, web and other platforms;
* A command of visual and communication design principles including typography, grid systems with experience applying this knowledge to digital experiences;
* Experience designing, building, maintaining and implementing pixel-perfect design systems;
* Ability to communicate design concepts through sketches and wireframes;
* Highly skilled in Figma, Sketch, Photoshop, Illustrator and other design tools;
* Preferably ability to animate in After Effects, have experience with Cinema 4D;
* Familiarity with software development processes and working in teams;
* Advanced knowledge of Swedish language;
* Upper-Intermediate level of English, both written and spoken.


**What Impact You’ll Make**
* Tailor design processes by applying the right methodologies at the right time;
* Proactively handle ambiguity, stay open-minded, willing to learn and ready to improvise;
* Control project timelines and manage expectations with the client;
* Apply wide-ranging design methods from research and ideation to hands-on design implementation;
* Facilitate output-orientated workshops with clients and team members;
* Be comfortable in a team-based environment locally and globally.


**What You’ll Get**
 Regardless of your position or role, we have in place a wide array of benefits including flexible working (hybrid/remote models) and generous time off policies to make it easier for all people to thrive and succeed at Star. On top of that, we offer an extensive rewarding and compensation package, intellectually and creatively stimulating space and some more.




